This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on stereo vision and depth estimation. Additionally, the paper mentions applications such as augmented reality and mobile autonomous robots, which are commonly associated with computer vision. 

The paper also discusses optimizations for energy-efficiency and performance, which suggests that it could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. 

The use of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) in the proposed algorithm and optimizations suggests that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The combination of classic stereo algorithms with DNNs and the proposed invariant-based stereo matching algorithm could also make this paper relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

Finally, the proposed optimizations for DNN inference could make this paper relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
